      {
        "type": "embed",
        "url": "https://twitter.com/corinne_podger/status/1103325073346383872",
        "html": "<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">.<a href=\"https://twitter.com/SeanDaganWood?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@SeanDaganWood</a> of <a href=\"https://twitter.com/PositiveNewsUK?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@PositiveNewsUK</a> says the media industry has known that positive news resonates with audiences for a long time, but has taken a while to learn how to approach it. Here&#39;s their approach. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/newsrw?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#newsrw</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/lqJRYKPVcj\">pic.twitter.com/lqJRYKPVcj</a></p>&mdash; ùêÇùê®ùê´ùê¢ùêßùêßùêû ùêèùê®ùêùùê†ùêûùê´üì±üéì (@corinne_podger) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/corinne_podger/status/1103325073346383872?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">March 6, 2019</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n",
        "embedType": "rich"
      },
      {
